LAMMPS (7 Feb 2024 - Update 1)
OMP_NUM_THREADS environment is not set. Defaulting to 1 thread. (src/comm.cpp:98)
  using 1 OpenMP thread(s) per MPI task
#TESTING the Water Box

#Initialization
units real
dimension 3 # 3D
atom_style full #Because charged
boundary p p p # periodic

#System definition
region box block -30 30 -30 30 -30 30
create_box 2 box bond/types 1 angle/types 1 extra/bond/per/atom 2 extra/angle/per/atom 1 extra/special/per/atom 2
Created orthogonal box = (-30 -30 -30) to (30 30 30)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
#          create_box 2 = two atom types
#           bond/types 1 = one bond type (O-H)
#           angle/types 1 = 1 angle type (O-H)
#           extra/bond/per/atom 2 (O bonds with two Hs)
#           extra/angle/per/atom 1 = each H2O has one angle
#           extra/special/per/atom 2 = each of the two H atoms can have individual interactions?
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Settings
molecule H2O tip3p.mol
Read molecule template H2O:
# Water molecule. TIP3P geometry
  1 molecules
  0 fragments
  3 atoms with max type 2
  2 bonds with max type 1
  1 angles with max type 1
  0 dihedrals with max type 0
  0 impropers with max type 0
#https://docs.lammps.org/Howto_tip3p.html

mass 1 15.999 #(type 1 = O, type 2 = H)
mass 2 1.008

fix 1 all nve #integrates constant amount of atoms, volume, energy
fix 2 all shake 0.0001 20 0 b 1 a 1 # (b 1 - bond type 1) (a 1 - angle type 1)
Finding SHAKE clusters ...
       0 = # of size 2 clusters
       0 = # of size 3 clusters
       0 = # of size 4 clusters
       0 = # of frozen angles
  find clusters CPU = 0.000 seconds

pair_style lj/cut/coul/long 2.5 #LJ + long-range Coulomb for 2.5 angstroms
kspace_style pppm 1.0e-4 #coulomb interactions beyond the cutoff

pair_coeff 1 1 0.1550 3.1536 # Sets LJ values epsilon, sigma (for O)
pair_coeff 2 2 0.0 1.0 # Sets LJ values epsilon, sigma (for H)

bond_style harmonic #harmonic/spring like bonds
bond_coeff 1 450.0 0.9572 #(1 = bond type) (450.0 = k [force constant]) (0.9572 = bond length)
angle_style harmonic
angle_coeff 1 55.0 104.52 #(1 = bond type) (55.0 = k [force constant]) (104.52 = angle)

create_atoms 0 random 100 12345 NULL mol H2O 12346 overlap 2.0 maxtry 30 # inserts water moleculess
Created 300 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (-30 -30 -30) to (30 30 30)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.003 seconds

